review_blob: Fruity and boozy, pours ruby/amber with a light foamy head. Medium lacing. I wouldve enjoyed this brew more if the alcohol was a bit more subdued, but I suppose it was an excellent intro to barley wines.

Rich, smooth, lightly carbonated chocolate stout. I couldnt really pick out the chili flavors, but certainly the vanilla and toasty nuttiness came through for me. I think this would be great warmed up.

Holy. Crap. This beer is effing RIDONKULOUS. Not a term I am apt to use, but one sniff and youll agree... that is, if you have any nosehair left! Hops beyond hell and back. Super bitter and tingly on the tongue. Beautiful pour with a thin, lingering white head and tight, delicate lacing. I couldnt do this beer again. A sipper and a sharer. Only the pros should attempt an entire bomber solo.
beer_name: Moylans Hopsickle Imperial India Pale Ale

review_blob: such a drinkable IPA, but with a knockout high abv %. Cloudy orange pour with a medium, lacy white head that dissipates quickly. Powerful citrus notes backed with solid malts and a lingering mouthfeel. Tingly and slick. Purchased as a 6 for around ten bucks you really cannot beat the value. Definitely worth your evening!

Endeavor bomber purchased at Specs DT. Smells like cat piss, very hoppy and citrusy DIPA. Medium, white head. nice lacing. Not worth a repeat, but I had to honor my home state on Texas Independence Day!
decent, drinkable ipa. hoppy and citrusy. nothing too spectacular of note, but worth sharing a pack with friends.

This is your basic, quality Imperial stout. Pours black with a light brown head and boy is this thing muddy. If you filled a pool with this beer you would never find your keys at the bottom. I mean, if you wanted to do something like that, but itd probably be best if you just drank it. Tasty molasses, coffee, caramel, and toffee flavors blend together in this heavily hopped and extra yeasty brew. Slick on the tongue, thick bodied but lively with the carbonation. A great balance of sweetness, acidity, and bitterness.

not bad, not great, but a decent saison. Pours cloudy amber with a thin white head. Sweet and acidic. Lightly malted, with an emphasis on citric flavors. I also noted a strong apple flavor. Basically this beer is an alcoholic fruit salad.
beer_name: Jester King Thrash Metal Farmhouse Strong Ale

review_blob: Solid DIPA from a quality brew co! While this isnt my favorite beer from Great Divide, they definitely deliver a great IPA with the Hercules. Heavily hopped, nutty and malty. The body is light and thin, perfectly carbonated and bitter. The taste hangs around long after your last sip, and I certainly didnt mind that. Balanced and clean. Would definitely try again.

This beer made a stout fan out of this traditionally IPA girl! I adore the heavy espresso and woody flavors of this edition of GDs Yeti Imperial Stout. Pours black and muddy with a creamy, light brown head. Super malty and toasty, soft and smooth on the tongue, bitter to the core. Sampled a friends bottle as I drank a completely subpar IPA, I became uber jealous I hadnt the foresight to pick one up for myself. I cannot wait to have this beer again.
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Espresso Oak Aged

review_blob: I was really impressed with the reviews of this beer so I made a priority to pick it up. At $5 or so a bottle, I figured "Hell yes! This is going to be a great night!"... then I opened the bottle. Pours light brown with a large, creamy off-white head, heavily particulate, the scent of yeast, hops, and malt invade your nostrils violently as this unfiltered rye settles into the glass. Notes of molasses and roasted nuts add a bit of depth to the aroma, but once it hits your lips the taste becomes very unappealing. I shared this beer with a buddy and he, too, was confused as to what exactly we were tasting. Thick and overly carbonated. I did not enjoy this beer much at all, but its not a complete drain-pour.
beer_name: Bear Republic Hop Rod Rye Ale

review_blob: like a citrus punch to the back of the throat! I really enjoyed this imperial, as part of the Avery Dictator series. Pours a cloudy ruby red, with a frothy white head that sticks around for more than a few sips. Heavy citrus, grapefruit, pineapple notes - tastes like a fruit juice cocktail Ive had before but I cant quite recall the name. Slightly sticky on the tongue, lively carb with a bitter finish. Heavily acidic. Very unique IIPA!
beer_name: Avery The Maharaja Imperial India Pale Ale

review_blob: I didnt enjoy drinking this IPA. Ive heard such wonderful talk of Left Coast, but this just didnt do anything for me. Very indistinguishable, unappealing flavor. Maybe I got a bad bottle.
My favorite Amber. Hoppy, crisp, thick, frothy head, although a slight metallic smell/aftertaste in some batches. A definite go-to at just about any bar in Texas. Really like this beer.
Roasty, lightweight Amber. Bitter aftertaste, feels very uninspired. This beer just put me off.
Truly not a completely unfortunate hefeweizen. I enjoyed it. A lot of flavor for a light brew. Wheaty and fruity.

The official beer of Texas. Ive grown up on this bock, I adore the Shiner brewing company for marketing tasty, upscale grocery store beverages for the average citizen. I may have grown beyond this simple, light bock, but it will always have a special place in my heart and refrigerator. Seeing an ice-cold pint of Shiner Bock slide across the table is always a welcome sight when Im out with friends. Buy a lightweight out-of-towner  this beer with a welcome "howdy" and shoot some darts or something.
Drink a regular shiner and just skip the greasy bar food if calories are your concern. I would just as well drink a Natty Light. Dont do this to yourself, you deserve better.

let me start off by saying I am not a stout fan. This brew is so deep and rich I still have to recommend it. Smells like a coffee shop after the employees held a raging kegger. Thick and smooth going down, can definitely pick up on caramel, chocolate, coffee, and smoky pit flavors.
another ballsy brew from Jester King. Bitter, dry, and very hoppy. Crisp finish. Little alcohol taste despite the high ABV. Looking forward to having this beer again.

I really dig this simple little IPA. Im not sure why, but the citrusy notes really resonated with me. I dont have much experience with New Belgium outside of Fat Tire, but this beer made me want to explore more of their brews. Well done.

DELICIOSO! I squealed after tasting this heavy brown ale. I dont know why, but I was compelled to get Italian. This beer isnt Italian. Its definitely a hoist up the stars and stripes American, with cedar undertones and a ballsy, robust flavor. I kept wanting another sip to sort out the complex profile fully.  A very interesting brew that I hope to revisit soon.

A very strong quadruple-Belgian with a beautiful pour, you can definitely taste the cherry undertones and strong scents of Bourbon from the aging process. Definitely not for the timid, I would suggest sharing a bottle among friends after dinner. The flavor is so strong it would interfere with most foods it seems. I personally would not drink this beer again, but that is simply because I find it to be too sweet for my liking.
Fun little wheat beer. Not too heavy, but substantial enough to make an impression as it goes down. This beer always brings a smile to my lips, something about it just feels good!

meh. Your traditional pale ale hopped up a little bit. Itd be great for a really hot summer day on the river with friends... if your friends like top 40 and network tv. Not undrinkable, but very lackluster.
beer_name: Real Ale Rio Blanco Pale Ale

review_blob: This... beverage... my God. Horrendous. It pours out purple like a bastardized boozy Kool-Aid. I was taken aback by how undrinkable this lager is. I couldnt get past two sips. If you want a fruity drink just get a lambic and pass on flavored lagers. I cant imagine this being tasty to anyone. Anywhere.

pretty decent Amber. Can taste the caramel. Refreshing, ordinary, something to add a bit of flair to an otherwise dull drinking affair. Ive given this beer to pedestrian beer consumers and theyve enjoyed it. I just hope they dont think the flavor train ends there!
what a boring beer!! Nothing distinguishable about this bock. Watery and flat. Tastes like a half-assed Shiner.
this IPA has a very distinct flavor unlike any Ive sampled before. Malty, woodsy. Not the best, but worth a taste.

To me, this IS the best IPA in America...that Ive tried so far. Hands down impeccable flavor, super hoppy and dry, harmoniously infused citrus notes, tickles the gums and just puts a smile on my face. Quality brew, high ABV at a reasonable price that goes down so damn smooth. If you want that out at the GOOD beer bar (you know the one!) feeling, bring a four pack of these babies home with you.

Great everyday IPA, I prefer the 90-minute brew, but this one is much easier to locate at grocery stores for a quick grab on the way home. Dogfish Head consistently amazes me with their attention to quality and high standards for all of their brews. Always happy to see one of these in the fridge at the bar or a buddys house. Clean, refreshing, deliciously hoppy but not off-putting to novice craft beer drinkers. The taste sticks with you. Introduce a buddy to crafts with this beer! He/she will thank you for it.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: the packaging/style sold me on this beer. Ive rarely had a bad beer from Magic Hat so I figured why not?. The brew could use some more balls, so to speak... it fell very flat and left me wanting a pull in either direction. A little sweet and heavy on the tongue, left me craving ice water. Had to try, wouldnt bother with again, though. Ive had significantly better Amber ales/spring seasonals.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: traditionally not an oktoberfest brew fan, but Id say this beer was worth a whirl.
tastes like walking through a forest with your mouth hanging open. The pine notes were too overpowering for my palate, I couldnt quite get past that to enjoy the beer.
great everyday IPA, slightly off aftertaste. great price, would buy again but Im not exactly rushing to the store.
This IPA  is among one of the best Ive tried to date. I wouldnt say it is perfect, but its certainly great for a few glasses and a good evening. Tastes like summer.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Double Wide I.P.A.
